This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with recognizing human activities from RGB-D videos. It also involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision research. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories due to the use of deep learning models and optimization methods. The multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with processing and analyzing videos. Finally, the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed model in interactions with humans.
